│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe transformation folds (icmp eq ctpop(X) 1) | (icmp eq X   │
│ 0) into (icmp ult ctpop(X) 2). The original expression is poison-safe because if X==0, │
│ the select chooses the true branch regardless of the ctpop comparison's poison state.  │
│ After folding, the single icmp uses ctpop directly; if ctpop carries poison-generating │
│ annotations (e.g., a range metadata that excludes 0), then ctpop(0) violates the range │
│ and becomes poison. This makes the target more poisonous than the source, which is     │
│ invalid.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nInstCombine replaces the select with a single     │
│ 'icmp ult %ctpop, 2'. The debug log shows that it erases the original cmp and notzero, │
│ and retains ctpop with its range metadata. Alive2 reports: for x=0, ctpop=0, but the   │
│ annotated range is 1..33, so the value is poison. The original select returns true     │
│ because notzero is true, masking the poison. The transformed code computes icmp ult on │
│ a poisoned ctpop, yielding poison, violating correctness.\n\n3. Root Cause             │
│ Analysis:\nThe root cause is that foldIsPowerOf2OrZero does not drop poison-generating │
│ annotations from the ctpop instruction before creating the new compare. A similar      │
│ transform in foldIsPowerOf2 explicitly calls dropPoisonGeneratingAnnotations() on the  │
│ ctpop instruction to ensure poison-safety and allows re-inference later. Here, the     │
│ lack of dropping causes the transformed result to depend on poison, making it more     │
│ poisonous than the original expression.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nEdit file       │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp lines 936-954 to drop          │
│ poison-generating annotations from the ctpop instruction before creating the new       │
│ compare, in both the 'and' (UGT) and 'or' (ULT) cases. Because this helper does not    │
│ have access to InstCombinerImpl (IC), we perform the drop unconditionally when the     │
│ ctpop operand is an Instruction.\n\nSuggested patch (conceptual):\n- After obtaining   │
│ CtPop = Cmp0->getOperand(0);\n- Insert:\n  if (auto *CtPopI =                          │
│ dyn_cast<Instruction>(CtPop))\n    CtPopI->dropPoisonGeneratingAnnotations();\n- Then  │
│ proceed to create the new compare (UGT/ULT). This mirrors the poison-safety handling   │
│ in foldIsPowerOf2.\n\nImplementation detail within the current lines:\n\nstatic Value  │
│ *foldIsPowerOf2OrZero(ICmpInst *Cmp0, ICmpInst *Cmp1, bool IsAnd,\n                    │
│ InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {\n  ...\n  Value *CtPop = Cmp0->getOperand(0);\n    │
